    <folder name="Application functions" id="id-d08ab5e154134d1cbb5f2fcf57e877a9">
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Explore scenarios + Filtering" id="id-ec7d1e85f87b4410ac1606d4df223b6d">
        <documentation>[F7] See summary dataset per city/area - * Show (aggregated) information (e.g. # roofs) and potential (e.g. #m2 potential for yellow roofs) 
=> you can select an area/zone and ask to show the totals of the roofs in that  area and sum of m2 (eg)
=> One can request a summary  on the current selection. A pop-window opens showing number of roofs and subtotal of m2 per rooftype + total m2

[F8] Click a roof to view its details => pop-up window opens with showing the details. Not a hoovering. 

[F9] If the data is available it's a must have. This also has effect to the preperation as one can add custom attributes (in diagram already). 
=> If available than option should be provided 'see current use'

[F11] &quot;>>> See [F9]
>>> If data is available and methodology is feasible:
* Show heritage, zoning, flood/heat/noise, grid and other constraints (e.g. as flags/filter or warning message).&quot;
=> 'Show constraints' with selection box of type of constraint. Expected behaviour is warning flag(s) for selected constraints.

[F12] See data recency: => Date showing how actual the data is (refresh date of the 3Dtile set, not the date of the underlying data sources)

[F13] &quot;Filter relevant roofs&quot;
* Potential (e.g. more than >x m2 of green roof); => filter on value and range (lower, between, higher)
* Owner type (e.g., private, housing corp, public); => filter on selected dropdown list one, all or selected
* Feasibility threshold => show by MRDV - indicator of certainty that you can realize a roof with a certain color. eg: 100% most likely does not show any roof, 10% shows more. 
=> Feasability score is calculated in the preperation and stored in thje 3Dtiles @@check with MRDV?
* Other attributes. => @@text search  - is nice-to-have?
@@Category selection - eg type of building -  is  nice-to-have?

[F16] &quot;During an interactive session with end-users, the end-user should be able to:
* Toggle scenario panel on/off => Select a scenario from the 3Dtiles
* Adjust model weights to reflect priorities and constraints for zones/ functions => Attributes filtering - as already described;
* Change feasibility thresholds for selected functions => type of rooftop
* Draw activation zones on the map => @@what is an activation zone?
* Set simple policy targets (e.g., minimal m2 of green roof) => Attribute filtering. 
* Save the calculated scenario and input parameters. => Open/Save Viewpoint functionality


[F19] 
@@One cannot add geo layers (like WMS, WMTS) layers as we are not creating a GIS tool.
@@One can only see one scenario at the same time in a browser tab, so no split screen. However it's possible to open a new tab in your browser and work on another scenario.

[F20] Rank opportunities: View top‑ranked areas/roofs/buildings per function => Attribute filtering based on properties (attribute:values)

[F21] Summarise results: View city/area/building‑level summary (m² by use, kWh, m³ retention, counts) => See first line.
[F21] See area (m²), slope (°), elevation (m) => @@Max will update catalog - part of first line here

[F24] View a concise methodology page => Click on a Info option in the browser, opens a HTML page with text explaining the meth
[F25] View a quick‑start guide => The info option contains a link to the meth and also a link to a quick start HTML page.

[A10] Provide a real-time, interactive engine for users to adjust weights and thresholds, draw zones, and see updated scenario results and KPIs within seconds.
</documentation>
        <property key="Potential technology solution" value="CesiumJS for 3D map canvas"/>
        <property key="Potential technology solution" value="A standard web framework (e.g., React or vanilla JS) for all other UI controls."/>
      </element>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Export analysis result" id="id-870eefc232f54fe29607e5914092030d">
        <documentation>[F22] Export data in CSV	&quot;
* Export calculation engine input data (CSV); => the totals after selecting a zone and summarize should be exportable to CSV
* Export selected roofs and building output dataset (CSV) => Just a table of buildings, roofs and properties (attribute:value). 

PDF is nice to have

If so, the source of the PDF is a CityJson file that contains aggregated values. The information for the report is collected from a CityJson file.

</documentation>
      </element>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Open / Save viewpoint" id="id-a387116121454f55adb75f387ee5b1d2">
        <documentation>A viewpoint consists of a visual representation of a presented scenario with the viewing settings and the values of the parameters.

Such that when reopening the 3D web viewer a user can select a viewpoint and start with where he/she left off with the same view. 
Visual: zoom level, angle, perspective. choosen scenario with the parameters / filters. This also makes it easier to compare scenarios as your look with the same parameters and perspective.
So one should be able to apply a viewpoint to a choosen scenario. And optionally save this viewpoint as a preference for viewing a scenario. 
</documentation>
      </element>
