        <folder name="Workpackages" id="id-430dac697bac47c68c3c12aab83abad1">
          <element xsi:type="archimate:WorkPackage" name="Develop MVP" id="id-a100379c57bd4710a9fa0ba75aed3950">
            <documentation>- The MVP must minimise scope and operational complexity while explicitly leaving room for future extensions.

Rationale
- Avoids overengineering, keeps costs down, and supports learning through pilots.
Derived from statements
- 5 ETL / Ingestion (no upload UI, specialist-driven)
- 11 Exports &amp; reporting (CSV/PDF only)
- 13 Security &amp; Privacy (baseline protections only)
- 15 Monitoring &amp; logging (basic, outside web app)
16 Build &amp; deploy (simple repos, basic CI)</documentation>
          </element>
          <element xsi:type="archimate:WorkPackage" name="Implement Scenario Engine" id="id-267da286ab7b4dbb856c6c5969d4c531">
            <documentation>Minimal scenario engine for MVP.</documentation>
          </element>
          <element xsi:type="archimate:WorkPackage" name="Prepare CityJSON dataset" id="id-1d821a6a528e4636878121b78876bf1d">
            <documentation>ETL + validation + ID generation.</documentation>
          </element>
          <element xsi:type="archimate:WorkPackage" name="Publish metadata and exports" id="id-ecf02552940047ee9483dab2c2051047">
            <documentation>DCAT-AP metadata + export formats.</documentation>
          </element>
        </folder>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:Plateau" name="MVP Plateau (31-12-2026)" id="id-ad0b132722ee423fa0971b39c9a8c2c1">
          <documentation>MVP delivered on 31-12-2026.</documentation>
